Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.17,0:15:00.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们变成了不同的物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They became different species.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.78,0:15:04.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是查尔斯 达尔文所说的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's what Charles Darwin meant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.88,0:15:08.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}物种起源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by "the origin of species."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.55,0:15:11.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}单个的熊不会进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An individual bear doesn't evolve;
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.12,0:15:15.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一群熊在几代繁衍中进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the population of bears evolves over generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.73,0:15:18.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果北极的冰日益减少\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the Arctic ice continues to dwindle
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.83,0:15:22.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}全球变暖的缘故 北极熊可能灭绝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}due to global warming, the polar bears may go extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.53,0:15:24.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们会被棕熊取代\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They'll be replaced by brown bears,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.57,0:15:27.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以更好地适应冰融后的环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}better adapted to the now defrosted environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.74,0:15:32.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个故事和狗的进化不一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is a different story from the one about the dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.24,0:15:34.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有人去指导这个变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No breeder guided these changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.74,0:15:38.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们都是由自然环境选择的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead, the environment itself selects them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.25,0:15:40.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是物竞天择\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is evolution by natural selection,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.92,0:15:44.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学历史上最颠覆性的理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the most revolutionary concept in the history of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.72,0:15:48.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1859年 达尔文首次提出了支持这个理论的证据\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin first presented the evidence for this idea in 1859.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.89,0:15:52.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它带来的争议从未消退\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The uproar it caused has never subsided.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.93,0:15:54.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why?
