Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.63,0:28:46.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}欢迎来到灭绝纪念堂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Welcome to the Halls of Extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.65,0:28:51.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}纪念着生命之树上的断枝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A monument to the broken branches of the Tree of Life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.46,0:29:05.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对于依然存在的上百万种生物来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For every single one of the millions of species
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.20,0:29:09.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可能上千种正在垂死挣扎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}alive today, perhaps a thousand others have perished.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.47,0:29:11.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们中大部分在与\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of them died out in the everyday competition
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.97,0:29:13.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其它生命形式的日常竞争中绝种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with other life-forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.54,0:29:17.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但也有很多是被地球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But many of them were swept away in vast cataclysms
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.14,0:29:19.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无法抗拒的大灾难灭绝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that overwhelmed the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.38,0:29:21.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在过去的5亿年里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the last 500 million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.81,0:29:24.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发生过5次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this has happened five times.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.50,0:29:27.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}奥陶纪(地质时代中显生宙古生代的第二个纪)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.00,0:29:29.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}泥盆纪(地质时代古生代中的第四个纪)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.70,0:29:32.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}三迭纪(中生代的第一个纪)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.30,0:29:35.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}白垩纪(地质年代中中生代的最后一个纪)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.00,0:29:37.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}二迭纪(古生代的最后一个地质时代)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.99,0:29:41.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.52,0:29:29.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}5次灭绝地球生命的大灾难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Five mass extinctions that devastated life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.72,0:29:34.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最惨的一次发生在2.5亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The worst one of all happened some 250 million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.99,0:29:37.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一个纪元的终结\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the end of an era
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.56,0:29:40.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}称之 二迭纪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}known as the Permian.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.38,0:29:59.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}三叶虫像装甲部队一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Trilobites were armored animals that hunted
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.15,0:30:01.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}成群结队的在海床上肆虐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in great herds across the seafloor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.65,0:30:04.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们是第一批进化出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They were among the first animals to evolve
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.35,0:30:06.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以成像的眼睛的动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}image-forming eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.33,0:30:13.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}三叶虫繁荣了大约2.7亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Trilobites had a good long run, some 270 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.36,0:30:16.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球曾是三叶虫的天下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth was once the planet of the trilobites.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.93,0:30:20.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但他们现在都没了 绝种了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But now they're all gone, extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.37,0:30:23.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们中最后的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The last of them were swept from life's stage
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.11,0:30:25.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也随着其它物种一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}along with countless other species
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.21,0:30:29.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在空前的环境灾难中绝种了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in an unparalleled environmental disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.96,0:30:41.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大灾难发生在今日西伯利亚的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The apocalypse began in what is now Siberia,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.59,0:30:46.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一场人类史上规模无比巨大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with volcanic eruptions on a scale unlike anything
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.26,0:30:48.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}的火山喷发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.88,0:31:03.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那时地球很不一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth was very different then,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.45,0:31:07.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有一个超质大陆板块和一片大洋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with one single supercontinent and one great ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.78,0:31:10.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无情的滚烫的熔浆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Relentless floods of fiery lava
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.29,0:31:13.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}洪水般吞没了比西欧还大的区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}engulfed an area larger than Western Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.09,0:31:17.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}断断续续的喷发持续了几十万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The pulsing eruptions went on for hundreds of thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.96,0:31:19.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}融化的岩石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The molten rock
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.56,0:31:22.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}点燃了煤层 并且 污染了大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ignited coal deposits and polluted the air
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.30,0:31:25.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}充斥着二氧化碳和其它温室气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with carbon dioxide and other greenhouse gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.96,0:31:30.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球温度升高 洋流停止了流动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This heated the Earth and stopped the ocean currents from circulating.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.36,0:31:47.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有害的细菌迅速繁殖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Noxious bacteria bloomed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.69,0:31:51.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海中其它生物几乎全部灭绝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but nearly everything else in the seas died.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.86,0:31:56.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}腐臭的水散发出致命的硫化氢气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stagnant waters belched deadly hydrogen sulfide gas into the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.93,0:31:59.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}导致大多数陆地生物窒息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which suffocated most of the land animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.48,0:32:16.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}百分之九十的物种灭绝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nine in ten of all species on the planet went extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.85,0:32:18.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们称之为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We call it...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.96,0:32:20.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}"大灭绝"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Great Dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.70,0:32:36.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上的生命差一点全部绝种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Life on Earth came so near to being wiped out
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.78,0:32:40.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}需要花费上千万年才能恢复\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it took more than ten million years to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.08,0:32:42.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是新的生命形式在慢慢进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But new life-forms slowly evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.41,0:32:46.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}开始填补由二迭纪大屠杀遗留的空缺\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to fill the openings left by the Permian holocaust.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.86,0:32:56.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恐龙就是其中的大赢家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Among the biggest winners were the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.76,0:32:59.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在地球是他们的天下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now the Earth was their planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.60,0:33:03.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们的统治持续了1.5亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Their reign continued for over 150 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.87,0:33:06.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也是在一次大灾难中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Until it, too, came crashing down
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.50,0:33:09.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不可避免的土崩瓦解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in another mass extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.44,0:33:12.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上的生命从太古时期就饱受摧残\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Life on Earth has taken quite a beating over the eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.08,0:33:14.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}却依然存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And yet it's still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.91,0:33:17.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命顽强得令人惊讶\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The tenacity of life is mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.75,0:33:20.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们总是能找到一条意想不到的生存之路\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We keep finding it where no one thought it could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.02,0:33:28.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到那条无名走廊吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That nameless corridor?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.36,0:33:30.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以后再说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's for another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.34,0:33:41.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有种动物可以活在沸腾的水中或者坚固的冰层中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I know an animal that can live in boiling water or in solid ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.64,0:33:44.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以10年不喝一滴水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can go ten years without a drop of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.04,0:33:46.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以不加防护的穿过寒冷真空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can travel naked in the cold vacuum
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.71,0:33:51.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并且充满强烈辐射的太空 而毫发无损\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and intense radiation of space and will return unscathed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.25,0:33:53.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}节肢动物 又叫  缓步类动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The tardigrade, or water bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.72,0:33:56.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生活在最高的高山还是最深的海沟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's equally at home atop the tallest mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.82,0:33:58.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对他们来说没有区别\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in the deepest trenches of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.66,0:34:01.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们生活在苔藓中  就在我们周围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in our own backyards, where they live among the moss
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.73,0:34:04.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}数也数不清\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in countless numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.23,0:34:05.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你可能从没注意到他们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You've probably never noticed them
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.63,0:34:07.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为他们太小了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because they're so small.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.13,0:34:08.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}差不多针尖大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About the size of a pinpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.77,0:34:10.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但他们很坚韧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But they're tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.50,0:34:14.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}节肢动物在所有的5次大灾难中幸存下来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The tardigrades have survived all five mass extinctions.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.81,0:34:17.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而他们则存在了5亿年之久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They've been in business for a half a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.57,0:34:19.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们一直认为生命很挑剔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We used to think that life was finicky,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.94,0:34:21.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他只能接受\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it would only take hold where it was
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.91,0:34:23.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不太冷 不太热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not too hot, not too cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.91,0:34:27.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不太暗 不咸 不酸 没辐射 的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not too dark or salty or acidic or radioactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.68,0:34:30.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有 不管怎么样 别忘了喝水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And whatever you do, don't forget to add water.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.49,0:34:32.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们错了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.26,0:34:33.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}节肢动物证明我们错了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the hardy tardigrade demonstrates,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.59,0:34:39.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命可以承受人类绝对无法生存的环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}life can endure conditions that would mean certain death for us humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.03,0:34:40.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我们和那些生活在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But differences between us and life found
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.86,0:34:43.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最极端环境下的生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in even the most extreme environments on our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.43,0:34:46.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有少许的区别\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are only variations on a single theme,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.44,0:34:48.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像一种语言中的不同方言\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dialects of a single language.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.01,0:34:51.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球生命的遗传密码\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The genetic code of Earth life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.71,0:34:59.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其它世界的生命又是什么样的呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what would life be like on other worlds?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.28,0:35:02.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有着完全不同历史的世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Worlds with a completely different history,
